Once there he started breaking store windows and yelling. When the police came to arrest him he started telling them about the concentration camp's existence and told them to arrest him, in jail he swallowed a spoon so they had to take him to the hospital, told the doctors there.

Reading about how the concentration camps under the communist regime in Bulgaria got closed because of one single total psychopath young guy who managed to hide under a truck driving materiel out of the camp, then sneaked out and somehow reached the capital city.

They sent him back to the camp but on the way he managed to swallow another spoon so they had to take him to a second hospital and he did the same thing there again. When they finally reimprisoned him at the concentration camp they knew word had gotten out so did nothing to him.

Some local party members who didn't know anything about the camp's existence came to visit him in the hospital and he told them everything, how they were being starved and tortured, all the guards were raping the women, all the typical gulag stuff. Party higher-ups came to listen

Afterwards there was a legal process, they closed down the camps, etc. Literally any single other course of action would have meant certain death. If he tried to hide somewhere they would have found him, but he played his cards with total perfection. God-tier survival instincts.
